    "The model is based on DL techniques that use a sequential neural model with the Adam optimization method.",
    "The records of 10140 students from three colleges in Assam, India were used to test the model.",
    "Compared to other classification methods such as AdaBoost and Artificial Immune Recognition System, the highest classification accuracy achieved was 95.34% produced by DNN techniques.",
    "Other results included a precision of approximately 0.96, recall of approximately 0.99, and F-Score of approximately 0.98.",
    "Using DL-based long-sequence generation, Wang et al (2020) addressed the issue of fine-grained student performance prediction in an online course by structuring the student's characteristics as a matrix with elements missing in some places."
